{
  "texts": [
    "Suppose R is admissible of order k ≤ k 0, n ∈ {0, 1,..., K -2} and Q = Q(R, n), Q ′ = Q(R, n + 1).",
    "Let r > 0 be the side length of Q and Q ′.",
    "Then for ρ k 0 = refine [k 0] ρ, we have | Q ρ k 0 - Q ′ ρ k 0 | ≥ r d (1 -5 1 K d-1) (5.21)Proof.",
    "Suppose n is even.",
    "If n is odd, the proof is analogous."
  ]
}